						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Slab in the back-yard of the Taluk Office.</hi></p>						

						<p>[Saṅka]ma—A.D. 1179.</p>						

						<p>This fragmentary and damaged record is dated in the king's <hi rend="bold">regnal year 3, Viḷambi, Māgha, s11u. 5, Monday,</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1179, January 15, Monday.</hi></p>						

						<p>The inscription records a gift, the details of which are lost, for the repairs to the temple of Svayaṁbhū-Lakshmaṇēśvara of <hi rend="bold">Huligere.</hi> The gift was entrusted to Trilōchana-paṇḍita.</p>						

						</summary>
